data.meta_description:
802 likes, 0 comments - cabcalloway on May 3, 2023: "A special 90th birthday shout out to the "Godfather of Soul", Mr. James Brown.

May 3, 1933 – December 25, 2006

One of the greatest entertainers of all time, James Brown tremendously influenced the trajectory of popular music. As a pioneer of funk, he charted 17 number one records and was honored as a seminal inductee of the @rockhall. 

In 1980, James and Cab both starred in the cult classic film "The Blues Brothers". @johnlandisofficial who directed The Blues Brothers, stated, "Cab Calloway is hip-hop." And so was James Brown and his classic vinyl breaks.

In 2015, @ed_piskor envisioned an illustrated Hip Hop Family Tree that documented early hip hop culture. Both Cab Calloway and James Brown were distinguished as "some of rapping's forefathers". We are excited for the new Hip Hop Family Tree Omnibus edition coming later this year. Respect the architects, thank you all for your inspiration!

#jamesbrown #godfatherofsoul #givethedrummersome #getonthescene #sayitloud #cabcalloway #edpiskor #hiphopfamilytree".
